The 'terpinenes' are a group of isomeric hydrocarbons that are classified as
terpenes. They each have the same molecular formula and carbon framework, but
they differ in the position of carbon-carbon double bonds. Î±-Terpinene has been
isolated from cardamom and marjoram oils, and from other natural sources. Î²-
Terpinene has no known natural source, but has been prepared synthetically from
sabinene. Î³-Terpinene and Î´-terpinene (also known as 'terpinolene') are natural
and have been isolated from a variety of plant sources.
